2 HOUSE BILL 971
1 (A) THERE IS AN ANNE ARUNDEL COUNTY CROWNSVILLE HOSPITAL
2 MEMORIAL PARK ADVISORY COMMITTEE.
3 (B) THE COMMITTEE CONSISTS OF THE FOLLOWING MEMBERS:
4 (1) ONE MEMBER REPRESENTING THE OFFICE OF THE GOVERNOR,
5 APPOINTED BY THE GOVERNOR;
6 (2) ONE MEMBER OF THE SENATE OF MARYLAND WHO REPRESENTS
7 THE DISTRICT IN WHICH THE CROWNSVILLE HOSPITAL MEMORIAL PARK IS
8 LOCATED, APPOINTED BY THE PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE;
9 (3) TWO MEMBERS OF THE HOUSE OF DELEGATES WHO REPRESENT
10 THE DISTRICT IN WHICH THE CROWNSVILLE HOSPITAL MEMORIAL PARK IS
11 LOCATED, APPOINTED BY THE SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE;
12 (4) ONE MEMBER OF THE ANNE ARUNDEL COUNTY COUNCIL WHO
13 REPRESENTS THE DISTRICT IN WHICH THE CROWNSVILLE HOSPITAL MEMORIAL
14 PARK IS LOCATED;
15 (5) ONE REPRESENTATIVE OF BOWIE STATE UNIVERSITY,
16 DESIGNATED BY THE PRESIDENT OF BOWIE STATE UNIVERSITY;
17 (6) THE ANNE ARUNDEL COUNTY BUDGET OFFICER, OR THE
18 BUDGET OFFICER’S DESIGNEE;
19 (7) THE DIRECTOR OF THE ANNE ARUNDEL COUNTY OFFICE OF
20 EQUITY AND HUMAN RIGHTS, OR THE DIRECTOR’S DESIGNEE; AND
21 (8) SEVEN MEMBERS APPOINTED BY THE COUNTY EXECUTIVE OF
22 ANNE ARUNDEL COUNTY WITH AT LEAST:
23 (I) ONE REPRESENTATIVE WITH EXPERTISE IN CULTURAL
24 HISTORY;
25 (II) ONE REPRESENTATIVE WITH EXPERTISE IN RECREATION
26 AND PARKS;
27 (III) ONE REPRESENTATIVE WITH EXPERTISE IN
28 INFRASTRUCTURE;

HOUSE BILL 971 3
1 (IV) ONE REPRESENTATIVE WITH EXPERTISE IN HEALTH AND
2 WELLNESS;
3 (V) ONE REPRESENTATIVE WHO REPRESENTS THE
4 COMMUNITIES ADJACENT TO THE CROWNSVILLE HOSPITAL MEMORIAL PARK; AND
5 (VI) ONE REPRESENTATIVE WITH EXPERTISE IN CIVIL RIGHTS.
6 (C) THE CHIEF ADMINISTRATIVE OFFICER OF ANNE ARUNDEL COUNTY
7 SHALL SERVE AS AN EX OFFICIO NONVOTING MEMBER OF THE COMMITTEE.
8 (D) THE COUNTY EXECUTIVE OF ANNE ARUNDEL COUNTY SHALL
9 DESIGNATE THE CHAIR OF THE COMMITTEE.
10 (E) THE COMMITTEE SHALL:
11 (1) ACT AS AN ADVISORY BODY AND PROVIDE ADVICE ON THE
12 PLANNING PROCESS, INCLUDING COMMUNITY INVOLVEMENT, FOR CROWNSVILLE
13 HOSPITAL MEMORIAL PARK TO:
14 (I) THE ANNE ARUNDEL COUNTY DELEGATION TO THE
15 GENERAL ASSEMBLY;
16 (II) THE COUNTY EXECUTIVE OF ANNE ARUNDEL COUNTY;
17 (III) THE COUNTY COUNCIL OF ANNE ARUNDEL COUNTY; AND
18 (IV) THE DEPARTMENTS OF THE ANNE ARUNDEL COUNTY
19 GOVERNMENT;
20 (2) MAKE RECOMMENDATIONS REGARDING THE DEVELOPMENT OF
21 THE CROWNSVILLE HOSPITAL MEMORIAL PARK THAT TAKE INTO ACCOUNT:
22 (I) THE CROWNSVILLE HOSPITAL MEMORIAL PARK MASTER
23 PLAN;
24 (II) THE CULTURAL HISTORY OF THE SITE;
25 (III) THE HEALTH AND WELLNESS OF THE RESIDENTS OF ANNE
26 ARUNDEL COUNTY;
27 (IV) THE RECREATION AND PARK NEEDS OF THE RESIDENTS OF
28 ANNE ARUNDEL COUNTY; AND

4 HOUSE BILL 971
1 (V) THE INFRASTRUCTURE NECESSARY TO SUPPORT ITEMS (I)
2 THROUGH (IV) OF THIS ITEM;
3 (3) COLLECT AND COMPILE PUBLIC INPUT ON THE DEVELOPMENT OF
4 THE CROWNSVILLE HOSPITAL MEMORIAL PARK; AND
5 (4) MAKE RECOMMENDATIONS TO ENSURE THAT THE CROWNSVILLE
6 HOSPITAL MEMORIAL PARK IS A PLACE THAT:
7 (I) FOCUSES ON MENTAL AND PHYSICAL HEALTH AND
8 WELL–BEING;
9 (II) IS INTENTIONAL AND EQUITABLE IN PROVIDING ACCESS TO
10 THE PROPERTY;
11 (III) IS TRUTHFUL ABOUT THE HISTORY OF CROWNSVILLE
12 HOSPITAL;
13 (IV) PRESERVES AND CELEBRATES THE NATURAL BEAUTY OF
14 THE PROPERTY;
15 (V) PROTECTS AND RESTORES THE BEST OF THE PROPERTY’S
16 BUILT ENVIRONMENT; AND
17 (VI) CULTIVATES EDUCATIONAL OPPORTUNITIES.
18 (F) ON OR BEFORE FEBRUARY 1 EACH YEAR, THE COMMITTEE SHALL
19 REPORT ITS ACHIEVEMENTS, FINDINGS, AND RECOMMENDATIONS TO THE COUNTY
20 EXECUTIVE OF ANNE ARUNDEL COUNTY, THE COUNTY COUNCIL OF ANNE
21 ARUNDEL COUNTY, AND, IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE
22 GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, THE ANNE ARUNDEL COUNTY DELEGATION TO THE
23 GENERAL ASSEMBLY.
24 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
25 October 1, 2025. It shall remain effective for a period of 5 years and, at the end of September
26 30, 2030, this Act, with no further action required by the General Assembly, shall be
27 abrogated and of no further force and effect.

